column6: from beside, by the side of, by, beside
column8: A primary preposition; properly, near; i.e. (with genitive case) from beside (literally or figuratively), (with dative case) at (or in) the vicinity of (objectively or subjectively), (with accusative case) to the proximity with (local (especially beyond or opposed to) or causal (on account of) -- above, against, among, at, before, by, contrary to, X friend, from, + give (such things as they), + that (she) had, X his, in, more than, nigh unto, (out) of, past, save, side...by, in the sight of, than, (there-)fore, with. column3:
Verb
Phonetic Spelling: (play\'-tho)
Definition: furnish, accomplish, fill, supply
Usage: I fill, fulfill, complete.
HELPS Word-studies

4130 pl\xe1\xb8\x97th\xc5\x8d (or pimpl\xc4\x93mi) \xe2\x80\x93 properly, fill to the maximum (full extent), "the limit" (CBL). 4130 /pl\xe1\xb8\x97th\xc5\x8d ("full") implies "filled to one\'s (individual) capacity."

[This root (pl\xc4\x93-) expresses totality, and implies full quantity ("up to the max"). DNTT (1,733) notes its cognates (pl\xc4\x93r\xc4\x93s, pl\xc4\x93ro\xc5\x8d, pl\xc4\x93r\xc5\x8dma) all come from the root (pl\xc4\x93-/pl\xc4\x93th\xc5\x8d) meaning "full in quantity." Thus 4130 /pl\xe1\xb8\x97th\xc5\x8d ("to fill or complete") refers to "that which is complete in itself because of plentitude, entire number or quantity.\xc2\xa0.\xc2\xa0.\xc2\xa0.\xc2\xa0the whole aggregate," WS, 395,96).

4130 (pl\xc4\x93th\xc5\x8d) may be a by-form derived from the same root as pimpl\xc4\x93mi. All these terms (cognates) emphasize the idea of "maximum (full extent)."]

Curtius, \xc2\xa7 366)): 1 aorist \xe1\xbc\x94\xcf\x80\xce\xbb\xce\xb7\xcf\x83\xce\xb1; passive, 1 future \xcf\x80\xce\xbb\xce\xb7\xcf\x83\xce\xb8\xce\xae\xcf\x83\xce\xbf\xce\xbc\xce\xb1\xce\xb9; 1 aorist \xe1\xbc\x90\xcf\x80\xce\xbb\xce\xae\xcf\x83\xce\xb8\xce\xb7\xce\xbd; from Homer on; the Sept. for \xd7\x9e\xd6\xb8\xd7\x9c\xd6\xb5\xd7\x90, also for \xd7\x94\xd6\xb4\xd7\xa9\xd6\xb0\xd7\x82\xd7\x91\xd6\xb4\xd6\xbc\xd7\x99\xd7\xa2\xd6\xb7 (to satiate) and passive, \xd7\xa9\xd6\xb8\xd7\x82\xd7\x91\xd6\xb7\xd7\xa2 (to be full); to fill: \xcf\x84\xce\xaf, Luke 5:7; \xcf\x84\xce\xaf \xcf\x84\xce\xaf\xce\xbd\xce\xbf\xcf\x82 (Winer\'s Grammar, \xc2\xa7 30, 8 b.), a thing with something, Matthew 27:48; (John 19:29 R G); in the passive, Matthew 22:10; Acts 19:29; (\xe1\xbc\x90\xce\xba \xcf\x84\xe1\xbf\x86\xcf\x82 \xe1\xbd\x80\xcf\x83\xce\xbc\xe1\xbf\x86\xcf\x82, John 12:3 Tr marginal reading; cf. Winers Grammar, as above note; Buttmann, \xc2\xa7 132, 12). what wholly takes possession of the mind is said to fill it: passive, \xcf\x86\xce\xbf\xce\xb2\xce\xbf\xe1\xbf\xa6, Luke 5:26; \xce\xb8\xce\xac\xce\xbc\xce\xb2\xce\xbf\xcf\x85\xcf\x82, Acts 3:10; \xe1\xbc\x80\xce\xbd\xce\xbf\xce\xaf\xce\xb1\xcf\x82, Luke 6:11; \xce\xb6\xce\xae\xce\xbb\xce\xbf\xcf\x85, Acts 5:17; Acts 13:45; \xce\xb8\xcf\x85\xce\xbc\xce\xbf\xe1\xbf\xa6, Luke 4:28; Acts 3:10; \xcf\x80\xce\xbd\xce\xb5\xcf\x8d\xce\xbc\xce\xb1\xcf\x84\xce\xbf\xcf\x82 \xe1\xbc\x81\xce\xb3\xce\xaf\xce\xbf\xcf\x85, Luke 1:15, 41, 67; Acts 2:4; Acts 4:8, 31; Acts 9:17; Acts 13:9. prophecies are said \xcf\x80\xce\xbb\xce\xb7\xcf\x83\xce\xb8\xe1\xbf\x86\xce\xbd\xce\xb1\xce\xb9, i. e. to come to pass, to be confirmed by the event, Luke 21:22 G L T Tr WH (for Rec. \xcf\x80\xce\xbb\xce\xb7\xcf\x81\xcf\x89\xce\xb8\xe1\xbf\x86\xce\xbd\xce\xb1\xce\xb9). time is said \xcf\x80\xce\xbb\xce\xb7\xcf\x83\xce\xb8\xe1\xbf\x86\xce\xbd\xce\xb1\xce\xb9, to be fulfilled or completed, i. e. finished, elapsed, Luke 1:23, 57 (Winers Grammar, 324 (304); Buttmann, 267 (230)); f; so \xd7\xa0\xd6\xb4\xd7\x9e\xd6\xb0\xd7\x9c\xd6\xb8\xd7\x90, Job 15:32; and \xd7\x9e\xd6\xb4\xd7\x9c\xd6\xb5\xd6\xbc\xd7\x90 to (ful-)fill the time, i. e. to complete, fill up, Genesis 29:27; Job 39:2. (Compare: \xe1\xbc\x90\xce\xbc\xcf\x80\xce\xaf\xcf\x80\xce\xbb\xce\xb7\xce\xbc\xce\xb9.)
